result.execSummary:
All charges against Tina Noodwang in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tina Noodwang is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:57 PM Defendant Tina Noodwang in court.  Attorney Russ S. Kort in court for Tina Noodwang.  Prosecuting attorney Austin M Mogard in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Investigator Matthews is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being an Investigator for the Wood County Sheriff's Department. Testifies to conducting a search warrant because there was probable cause to believe drugs were being sold and used in and from the residence. Testifies to whom he made contact w/ in the residence. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Testifies to learning who lives at the residence and lists the people that lived there. The defendant is one of the ones that resides there. Testifies to what was found during the search warrant. Testifies to being informed who used and who purchase and sell the substances. Testifies to a statement being made regarding people outside of the household coming to purchase the substances. 
Attorney Kort cross examines the witness. Testifies to the home being surveillance before the search warrant was executed. Testifies to not finding that the defendant was using or selling drugs. Testifies to the criminal complaint statements. Testifies to the residence. 
Attorney Mogard questions the witness.

Attorney Kort makes an argument against the charges. 
Attorney Mogard makes an argument that the State has met their burden of proof.

Due to no proof of the defendant having knowledge of drugs being sold from the residence, this case is dismissed.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on October 12, 2022 at 02:15 pm.
